{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b0297277-4317-4575-be44-31f61c165f0f","content":"The issue is file ordering in the `.fsproj`. In F#, compilation order matters — `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Domain.fs` is listed after `Services.fs`. Let me fix it:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_pVo1189ew1fh1FVumICuCY","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-25bc682c7b2d466fa10050d8d616475f/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-25bc682c7b2d466fa10050d8d616475f/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"3da54385-73ae-445e-b478-8d29f193558a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n```xml\n<Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n```\n\n`Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` is listed *after* `Services.fs`. The fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":415,"requestId":"7C1D:9309E:AC625A:C50931:6A0279A8"},"id":"208e32de-c2d3-4717-a9cf-1c1751b568e6","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:52:00.337Z","parentId":"11218ae2-3302-4f82-af37-be8a5373f0f1"}
